	(138, 763942046, 0, 0, 'User: переведи на русский\nChatGPT: \nРешение уравнения: x = pi/2 (пи/2).', 'User: Решите уравнение sin^2 x/2 - cos^2 x/2 = cos2x\nChatGPT: \nHello there! To solve this equation, we can use the identity sin^2 (x/2) - cos^2 (x/2) = cos (2x). This identity states that the left side of the equation is equal to the right side, so we can set the two sides equal to each other and solve for x. We get:\n\nsin^2(x/2) - cos^2(x/2) = cos (2x)\nsin^2(x/2) = cos (2x) + cos^2(x/2)\nsin^2(x/2) = 1 + cos^2(x/2) \nsin^2(x/2) - 1 = cos^2(x/2)\nsin^2(x/2) - cos^2(x/2) = 1\nsin^2(x/2) - cos^2(x/2) = cos (2x)\n\nThus, we can solve for x by setting the two sides equal to each other and solving for x:\n\n2x = cos^-1 (sin^2(x/2) - cos^2(x/2))\n2x = cos^-1 (1)\n2x = pi\n\nTherefore, the solution to the equation is x = pi/2.', ''),
